Even though he did not blush at his own manifest falsehood, Battus was unable to betray Mercury to the god himself in disguiseÍ¾ indeed, the fast- talking rustic was quickly outwitted and suffered the punishment consequent upon such mad behavior. If we are for the moment to give proper credence to the words of Antiquity, Mercury perma- nently metamorphosed the madly audacious liar into silent flint. Thus he put a well-deserved end to Battus's mendacity. But even men of higher station have suffered the brunt of punishment for lies.
